<div class="row g-4">
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card section-card h-100">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/6009194/pexels-photo-6009194.jpeg"
                 class="card-img-top" alt="Ganesh Chaturthi celebrations">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Ganesh Chaturthi</h5>
                <p class="card-text text-muted">
                    One of the biggest festivals in Maharashtra, dedicated to Lord Ganesha. Colourful idols
                    are installed in homes and public pandals, followed by cultural programs, music, and
                    immersion processions (visarjan) in rivers and the sea.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card section-card h-100">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/7476190/pexels-photo-7476190.jpeg"
                 class="card-img-top" alt="Traditional Gudi during Gudi Padwa">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Gudi Padwa</h5>
                <p class="card-text text-muted">
                    Gudi Padwa marks the Maharashtrian New Year and the beginning of the spring season.
                    Families decorate their homes with rangoli, raise a decorative Gudi flag, wear
                    traditional attire and prepare festive dishes.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row g-4 mt-1 mt-md-3">
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card section-card h-100">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/10784028/pexels-photo-10784028.jpeg"
                 class="card-img-top" alt="Lavani folk dance performance">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Lavani &amp; Folk Arts</h5>
                <p class="card-text text-muted">
                    Lavani is a traditional folk dance form known for its powerful rhythm and expressive
                    storytelling, often performed with dholki drums. Other folk arts include Tamasha,
                    Powada ballads and Koli dance of coastal fishing communities.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card section-card h-100">
            <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/6750424/pexels-photo-6750424.jpeg"
                 class="card-img-top" alt="Women in traditional Nauvari saree">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Language &amp; Attire</h5>
                <p class="card-text text-muted">
                    Marathi is the official language of Maharashtra, with rich literature and theatre.
                    Traditional attire includes the Nauvari saree for women and dhoti-kurta or kurta-pyjama
                    for men, often accompanied by the distinctive pheta (turban).
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

